    slug: "muti-e-azam",
    description: `Muti e Azam is a comprehensive and deeply researched Urdu-language Islamic book that explores the extraordinary life, character, and lasting legacy of the greatest military commander in the history of Islam, Hazrat Khalid bin Waleed (may Allah be pleased with him), who was honoured by Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) with the title "Saifullah" — the Sword of Allah. This book presents a thorough biographical account that traces Khalid bin Waleed's journey from his early days in the Banu Makhzum clan of the Quraysh, through his initial opposition to Islam, to his remarkable conversion and subsequent elevation as one of the most brilliant military strategists the world has ever known. The author draws upon authentic historical sources including classical works of seerah, hadith compilations, and the writings of early Islamic historians to reconstruct the major events and campaigns of Khalid's life with scholarly precision and narrative flair. The book covers in detail the pivotal battles in which Khalid bin Waleed played a decisive role, including the Battle of Uhud where he commanded the Makkan cavalry, the Battle of Mu'tah where his tactical genius saved the Muslim army from annihilation, the conquest of Makkah, the Battle of Hunayn, the Siege of Ta'if, and the monumental Battles of Yarmouk and al-Qadisiyyah that opened the lands of Syria and Persia to Islam. Each military campaign is analysed not merely as a historical event but as a case study in leadership, strategy, courage, and faith, with the author highlighting how Khalid's deep trust in Allah and his unwavering commitment to Islamic principles informed his every decision on and off the battlefield. The book also examines the lesser-known aspects of Khalid's character, including his humility despite his fame, his piety, his treatment of prisoners and civilians, his respect for other commanders, and the grace with which he accepted his eventual dismissal from military command by the second Caliph, Umar ibn al-Khattab. Written in eloquent Urdu that brings historical events to vivid life, this book is an essential read for students of Islamic history, military enthusiasts, and anyone who wishes to understand how faith and valour combined to shape the course of civilisation during the golden age of Islam.`,
