    slug: "muwatta-imam-malik-rawayat-ibn-al-qasim",
    description: `Muwatta Imam Malik — Rawayat Ibn al-Qasim is an authoritative edition of one of the earliest and most revered hadith collections in Islam, transmitted through the specific narration chain of Imam Ibn al-Qasim, who was one of the foremost students of Imam Malik ibn Anas (may Allah have mercy on them both). The Muwatta of Imam Malik holds a unique position in Islamic literature as the first systematically organised book of hadith and fiqh, compiled in the second century of the Islamic era in the city of Madinah. Imam Malik spent over forty years compiling this work, carefully selecting approximately seventeen hundred narrations from the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him), the companions, and the successors, organising them according to chapters of Islamic law that cover the full spectrum of worship, transactions, family law, criminal law, and social conduct. This particular edition presents the text as transmitted by Abdullah ibn al-Qasim, a devoted student who studied under Imam Malik for approximately twenty years and was considered one of the most reliable narrators of the Muwatta. Ibn al-Qasim's transmission is especially valued in the Maliki school of Islamic jurisprudence, as he became the primary conduit through which Imam Malik's legal methodology and opinions were preserved and transmitted to subsequent generations of scholars in Egypt and North Africa. The book covers essential topics including the purification (taharah) and prayer (salah), the obligatory charity (zakat), fasting during Ramadan, the pilgrimage (hajj), marriage and divorce, commercial transactions, inheritance, judicial proceedings, and the etiquettes of daily life. Each chapter begins with the relevant Quranic verses, followed by prophetic narrations, statements of the companions, and the legal opinions and reasoning of Imam Malik, providing readers with a complete picture of how Islamic law was understood and practised in the city where the Prophet himself lived and taught. The chain-based narration methodology of this edition preserves the scholarly rigour of classical Islamic scholarship, making it an indispensable resource for advanced students of hadith, scholars of Islamic jurisprudence, and anyone interested in understanding the foundational sources of Maliki fiqh. This edition is produced with careful attention to textual accuracy and readability, ensuring that this timeless work remains accessible to serious students of Islamic knowledge in the contemporary era.`,
    metaDescription: "Muwatta Imam Malik Rawayat Ibn al-Qasim is an authoritative hadith and fiqh collection transmitted through Imam Malik's foremost student."
