    description: `Muwatta Imam Malik — Rawayat Ibn al-Qasim (Imported Edition) is a premium quality imported printing of the celebrated hadith and fiqh compilation originally authored by Imam Malik ibn Anas and transmitted through the reliable chain of his distinguished student Ibn al-Qasim. This imported edition distinguishes itself through superior printing quality, premium paper, and meticulous typesetting that enhances the reading experience for scholars, students, and researchers who engage deeply with classical Islamic texts. The Muwatta of Imam Malik is universally recognised as one of the foundational works of Islamic scholarship, representing the earliest attempt to systematically organise the narrations of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) alongside the legal reasoning of the scholars of Madinah. Imam Malik compiled this work over a period of more than four decades, drawing upon his unparalleled access to the scholars and students of the city of Madinah who had directly learned from the companions of the Prophet. The Rawayat Ibn al-Qasim version is particularly significant because Ibn al-Qasim studied under Imam Malik for approximately twenty years, making him one of the longest-serving and most knowledgeable students of the great imam. His narration of the Muwatta became the primary reference for the Maliki school of jurisprudence in Egypt and the Maghreb, and through his students such as Sahnun ibn Sa'id, the Maliki madhhab spread throughout North Africa, West Africa, and parts of the Muslim world. This imported edition presents the complete text with enhanced formatting that makes the hadith narrations, chains of transmission, and legal commentary easier to follow and study. The high-quality binding ensures durability for repeated use in study circles, academic research, and personal reference. The content covers the major chapters of Islamic law including purification, prayer, funerals, charity, fasting, pilgrimage, trade, marriage, crimes, and judicial proceedings, with each topic addressed through Quranic evidence, prophetic narrations, and the considered opinions of Imam Malik and the scholars of Madinah. For serious students of Islamic studies who demand the highest quality in both content and presentation, this imported edition of the Muwatta represents an excellent addition to any Islamic library, combining the timeless wisdom of one of Islam's greatest scholars with modern printing standards that honour the dignity of the text.`,
