    slug: "my-creator",
    description: `My Creator is a thoughtfully designed children's Islamic book that introduces young minds to the fundamental concept of Allah as the Creator of everything in existence, laying the foundation for a child's understanding of Tawheed — the oneness of God — in a manner that is both age-appropriate and spiritually enriching. The book takes children on a journey of discovery, encouraging them to look at the world around them with wonder and appreciation as they learn about the countless signs of Allah's creative power that are visible in nature and in their own lives. Through simple yet profound text, the book explains how Allah created the heavens and the earth, the sun and the moon, the mountains and the oceans, the plants and the animals, and ultimately human beings themselves, presenting each act of creation as a manifestation of Allah's wisdom, power, and limitless mercy. The narrative helps children understand that everything they see, hear, touch, and experience is part of Allah's magnificent creation and that recognising the Creator behind creation is the first and most important step in a Muslim's spiritual journey. The book introduces core Islamic concepts such as gratitude (shukr) for Allah's blessings, the purpose behind creation, and the special status of human beings as Allah's khalifah (vicegerent) on earth, all explained in language that young children can easily grasp. Beautiful illustrations accompany the text, depicting scenes from nature and daily life that reinforce the message of each page. The illustrations are designed to be engaging and multicultural, reflecting the diversity of the global Muslim community while maintaining Islamic sensibilities. Each section includes a short du'a or dhikr that children can learn and recite, helping them develop the habit of remembering Allah throughout their day. The book also contains interactive elements such as simple questions that encourage children to think about and discuss what they have learned, making the reading experience participatory rather than passive. Parents and teachers will find this book to be an excellent starting point for conversations about faith, creation, and the attributes of Allah. Suitable for children aged three to seven, My Creator is an essential addition to every Muslim child's library, providing a gentle and loving introduction to the most important concept in Islam: knowing and loving the One who created us.`,
