    slug: "my-prayer-book",
    description: `My Prayer Book is a step-by-step children's guide to learning and performing the five daily Islamic prayers (Salah), designed to take young Muslims from their very first attempt at prayer to performing it correctly and confidently with full understanding of what they are saying and doing. This comprehensive instructional book breaks down the prayer into its individual components, explaining each movement (rukn) and recitation in a way that children can understand, remember, and practice. The book begins with the basics of prayer preparation, including the importance of wudu (ablution), the appropriate clothing for prayer, the direction of the qiblah, and the significance of praying at the prescribed times. It then walks the reader through each position of the prayer — standing (qiyam), bowing (ruku), prostration (sujud), and sitting (jalsah) — describing the physical posture, what to recite in each position, and the spiritual significance of each movement. Every Arabic recitation is presented in clear Arabic script alongside its English transliteration and a child-friendly explanation of its meaning, enabling children who are still learning Arabic to pray with understanding rather than merely imitating sounds. The book includes detailed illustrations showing children in each position of the prayer, providing visual reference that helps young learners confirm they are performing the movements correctly. Colour-coded sections differentiate between the obligatory (fard) and recommended (sunnah) elements of the prayer, helping children understand the structure and priorities of their worship. Special attention is given to common mistakes that children make when learning to pray, with clear instructions on how to avoid or correct them. The book also covers the supplications (du'as) recited after the prayer, including the tasbihat and the dua for forgiveness. A visual prayer chart is included that can be displayed on a wall as a daily reminder, and a progress tracker allows children to mark their improvement over time. The book addresses the different prayers of the day (Fajr, Dhuhr, Asr, Maghrib, and Isha) and explains the differences between them, including the number of units (rak'ahs) in each. Suitable for children aged five to twelve, My Prayer Book is an essential companion for every Muslim child's journey towards establishing the most important pillar of Islam after the declaration of faith.`,
    metaDescription: "My Prayer Book is a step-by-step illustrated children's guide to learning Salah with Arabic recitations, transliteration, and practical tips."
